Subject: [PATCH 1/2] powerpc/t4240: introduce kernel option T4240_QDS_SIMICS

When running a t4240qds on simics, we have to enable some workarounds.
So introduce a kernel option for this purpose.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/platforms/85xx/Kconfig |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/platforms/85xx/Kconfig b/arch/powerpc/platforms/85xx/Kconfig
index b308dbd..7be67ce 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/platforms/85xx/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/powerpc/platforms/85xx/Kconfig
@@ -348,6 +348,10 @@ config T4240_QDS
 	help
 	  This option enables support for the T4240 QDS board
 
+config T4240_QDS_SIMICS
+	bool "Enable SIMICS support for T4240QDS"
+	default n
+	depends on T4240_QDS
 endif
 endif # FSL_SOC_BOOKE
 
